  "description": [
    "VOL III NO 53 MORGANTOWN W VA MONDAY NOVEMBER 7 1898 TWO CENTS ABANDONS THE JOB Berry and Kidder throw up the contract on the streets Hare employed counsel and will sue the town The council is not afraid and will file counter suitsThey can show that the work was never satisfactory and that the engineer repeatedly re fused to accept itReport of White will come in today and the whole matter will be settled tonight The street paving about which there has been so much talk is still a fruitful source of news The con tractor has given the wheel another turn by leaving the job All the men that were connected with the work have gone home and the street which they had torn up is in a con dition to become a mud hole this winter if something is not done for it Berry and Kidder have retained Cox and Baker as their attorneys and will bring suit against the town for the remainder which has been held back on the Main street jobThe council paid them only fifty percent of the contract price and the other twenty which is due under the con tract will be"
  ],
